\f0 \par \pard\s3\li0\ri0\f0\fs22\cf0 Starting at SAS 9.4M9, you can enable Transport Layer Security (TLS) for internal connections through SAS Deployment Wizard. This includes communication between SAS Web Server, SAS Web Application Server, JMS Broker and Cache Locator servers.\f0\fs22\cf0  \f0\fs22\cf0 \par \f0\fs22\cf0 For more information, see\f0\fs22\cf0  \f0{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK https://go.documentation.sas.com/doc/en/bicdc/9.4/biig/n05020intelplatform00install.htm#p0aanc61cgjmqvn1mm4dr1s4r4i3}{\fldrslt \pard\f0\fs22\ul\cf4 (SAS 9.4M9) Use TLS for Internal Connections.\ul0 }}\f0\fs22\cf0 \par \par
\f0 \par \pard\s3\li0\ri0\f0\fs30\b\cf0 5\b0\f0\fs30\b\cf0  \b0\f0\fs30\b\cf0  \b0\f0\fs30\b\cf0  \b0\f0\fs30\b\cf0 Hardware Requirements\b0\par
\f0 \par \pard\s3\li0\ri0\f0\fs22\cf0 SAS is designed for analyzing small to very large volumes of data by doing large block sequential I/O. To ensure your hardware is optimally configured, SAS recommends that you review the information found in the\f0\fs22\cf0  \f0{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK https://support.sas.com/en/documentation/install-center/94/94-foundation-guides.html}{\fldrslt \pard\f0\fs22\ul\cf4 SAS 9.4 Foundation System Requirements.\ul0 }}\f0\fs22\cf0  \f0\fs22\cf0  \f0\fs22\cf0 \par \par
\f0 \par \pard\s3\li0\ri0\f0\fs22\cf0 \par \f0\fs22\cf0 Solutions might have additional requirements. They should be reviewed at\f0\fs22\cf0  \f0{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK https://support.sas.com/en/documentation/install-center/94/system-requirements.html}{\fldrslt \pard\f0\fs22\ul\cf4 SAS 9.4 System Requirements by Product.\ul0 }}\f0\fs22\cf0 \par \f0\fs22\cf0 \par \f0\fs22\cf0 For the best practices for your hardware, see\f0\fs22\cf0  \f0{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK https://sas.service-now.com/csm/en/tuning-guidelines-and-best-practices-for-your-hardware-infrastructure?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0036235}{\fldrslt \pard\f0\fs22\ul\cf4 Tuning guidelines and best practices for your hardware infrastructure.\ul0 }}\f0\fs22\cf0 \par \par
